text.tspan: Idea: Just draw all slides on one canvas
1. Create a new SVG in Inkscape
3. Add another layer and name it "Slides"
That's all you need! Now start drawing!
Put the title slide at the top left
Slides will be automatically ordered from
top to bottom and left to right.
The slide size does not matter.
(!) All <rect> tags in "Slides" will be treated as slide boundary
Navigate using Click, SPACE, LEFT, RIGHT, UP, DOWN,
PGUP,PGDOWN to navigate the sides. Press HOME to go
into overview mode. Click any slide in overview to open it.
Save and close + open SVG in external editor.
1. Add the xlink namespace to the <svg> tag (if not exists):
2. Add the two required script files: slides.js and jquery.js
Make sure the names and relative paths to the script are correct.
You need to do these steps only once!
1. Do not use too man different slide sizes and aspects. Otherwise you
will need to adjust font sizes all over the place to get a consitent look
2. Leave enough space bewteen slides, otherwise you may
see slide B peeking into the presentation canvas of slide A
3. Clone title + rect of your slides to create new slides. This
automatically puts content + rect in the correct layer.
Open the SVG file in Chrome or Firefox for viewing and presenting.
